[2] USA: Frontier Airlines expands Ebola notifications to 800 passengers
Date: Fri 17 Oct 2014
Source: WKYC [edited]
http://www.wkyc.com/story/news/health/2014/10/17/frontier-expands-ebola-notifications-to-800-passengers/17424245

Frontier Airlines is now notifying 800 passengers about potential Ebola exposure tied to the case of nurse AV, according to CNN. Wed [15 Oct 2014], Frontier initially issued passenger notifications to 132 travelers on board AV's return flight to Dallas from Cleveland on Mon [13 Oct 2014]. This expanded notification by Frontier encompasses passengers on both of AV's flights between Dallas and Cleveland along with 5 other flights with the same plane. Health officials say AV, 29, could have been symptomatic with Ebola as early as Friday, 10 Oct 2014, while she was visiting family in Tallmadge to plan her wedding. Despite these additional precautionary notifications by the airline, health officials say passengers stand a low risk of being infected. AV is currently being treated in Atlanta.

