******
[7] Prevention & false alarms

Colombia: cancels flights from West Africa because of Ebola
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The border shut down doesn't mean people can't return to Colombia if they have been visiting West Africa; what it means is that strict detainment protocols will be enacted for individuals under suspicion of having contact with the virus.... -- more
http://voxxi.com/2014/10/16/colombia-closes-borders-avoid-ebola

[I am reminded of what the president of one African country said to me when I introduced the WHO AIDS program to his country in the 1980s: "We do not have any cases. We'll just close our borders." The country had borders with 4 other countries, and of course the AIDS virus (HIV) got in. - Mod.JW]

--
USA: Travel ban for Texas health care workers in Ebola case
--------------------------------------------------------------------
17 Oct 2014: (USA Today) A health care worker who may have handled a specimen from the Liberian man who died from Ebola in Dallas, is currently on a cruise ship in the Caribbean. The U.S. government is working to get her and her husband back home. Texas health officials have ordered any person who entered the room of the 1st Ebola patient at a Dallas hospital not to travel by public transport, including planes ship, buses or trains, or visit groceries, restaurants or theaters for 21 days, until the danger of developing Ebola has passed.
[Byline: Doug Stanglin]
http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/10/17/texas-ebola-health-care-workers-travel-ban/17424465

[This is said to be voluntary. But if one person breaches the order, are they all liable to be treated like the NBC reporter and her team and put under mandatory quarantine? I don't see how it could be practical to enforce it. See also comment in [3] above. - Mod.JW]

--
USA: Obama Authorizes National Guard Call-Up to Fight Ebola in West Africa
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
16 Oct 2014: (Newsweek) President Barack Obama authorized a call-up of the National Guard and additional military reservists to active duty on Thursday [16 Oct 2014] in case they are needed to address the humanitarian crisis that has resulted from the Ebola outbreak in West Africa... to "augment the active forces in support of Operation United Assistance." Reservists would provide humanitarian assistance and "consequence management" related to the disease's outbreak in West Africa. [Byline: Lucy Westcott]
http://www.newsweek.com/president-obama-authorizes-national-guard-fight-ebola-west-africa-277991

--
USA: CDC lowers temperature threshold for Ebola fever to 100.4 F [38 C]
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
15 Oct 2014: (LA Times) Without explanation, the federal Centers for Disease Control and Prevention [CDC] has lowered its threshold for suspecting that someone might be infected with Ebola from 101.5 degrees F to 100.4 F [38 C].... According to CDC Director Thomas Frieden, 150 passengers per day -- or 1050 a week -- arrive in the U.S. from Liberia, Sierra Leone and Guinea.... -- more
http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-ebola-fever-20141015-story.html

[A degree less makes the difference now between free entry and entry with monitoring. Always assuming airport remote thermometers are checked more than once a day for accuracy. Can travelers challenge a high reading? - Mod.JW]

--
USA: Tests prove negative for Ebola in Yale graduate student
------------------------------------------------------------
16 Oct 2014: (BNC Connecticut) Connecticut Governor Malloy invokes public health emergency powers. "Dr. Mullen has made the determination that it is in the best interest for residents in New Haven and the surrounding area that the patient remain isolated as we await official test results from the CDC." ... The students were conducting research in the West African country where Ebola is widespread. They returned on Saturday, 11 Oct 2014, and have been kept in voluntary sequestration, said Laurence Grotheer, spokesperson for New Haven Mayor Toni Harp.... -- more
http://www.nbcconnecticut.com/news/local/Yale-New-Haven-Hospital-Admits-Person-with-Ebola-Like-Symptoms--279415262.html

[The accompanying audio clip says his isolation room has negative pressure, which filters any virus out of its exhaust air. This is excellent as an extreme precaution. - Mod.JW]

